  "text": "The concept of the 'Triple Bottom Line' [CITATION_1] or 3BL that seeks to integrate economic, social and environmental performance has been widely advocated in considering the sustainability of organizations and supply chains. [CITATION_2] define sustainable supply chain management as \"the strategic, transparent integration and achievement of an organization's social, environmental, and economic goals in the systemic coordination of key inter-organizational business processes for improving the long-term economic performance of the individual company and its supply chains\". Camarinha-Matos et al (2010) specify the three pillars in 3BL more concretely:",
